Package: salmonIPM
Title: Integrated Population Models for Pacific Salmon
Version: 1.3.3
Authors@R: as.person(c(
    "Eric Buhle <eric.buhle@noaa.gov> [aut, cre]", 
    "Mark Scheuerell <mark.scheuerell@noaa.gov> [aut]"
  ))
Description: Fits IPMs or run-reconstruction regressions representing anadromous 
    Pacific salmonid population dynamics using a hierarchical Bayesian framework 
    implemented in Stan. Various models are available, representing alternative 
    life-history structures and independent or hierarchically pooled populations.
    Users can specify stage-specific covariate effects and hyper-priors using formula syntax.
Depends:
    R (>= 4.2),
    rstan (>= 2.26.0),
    stats,
    gnorm
Imports:
    methods,
    Rcpp (>= 0.12.0),
    RcppParallel,
    rstantools (>= 2.0.0.9000),
    parallel,
    shinystan,
    posterior,
    loo,
    MASS
LinkingTo: 
    BH (>= 1.66.0),
    Rcpp (>= 0.12.0),
    RcppEigen (>= 0.3.3.3.0),
    RcppParallel,
    rstan (>= 2.18.1),
    StanHeaders (>= 2.18.0)
License: GPL (>= 3) + file LICENSE
